The paper deals with automated texture-based quantification of emphysema subtypes using unsupervised learning on a large heterogeneous database of CT scans. This involves image analysis and machine learning techniques, which are commonly associated with computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of unsupervised learning also suggests a possible association with artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also mentions the reproducibility of the texture prototypes across subjects, which could be related to the measurement science (cs.MS) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the interpretation of lung CT scans, which could be associated with multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
